Share this on WhatsAppSpread the love Yemi Osinbajo Support Network have promised to provide healthcare services to delegates during the APC presidential primary slated for June 6, 7 and 8.
 
Addressing a press conference on Thursday in Abuja, the Volunteer Coordinator of the PYO, Dr Obinna Ebirim, said medical doctors, nurses, community health extension workers (CHEW), laboratory officers and pharmacists would be available.
 
The services will be free of charge.
 
The PDP presidential primary was widely condemned for its heavy dollarization—as delegates received thousands of dollars to vote for aspirants.
 
Same experience has been observed in the APC whose primary comes up in about 60 hours from now.
 
V.P Yemi Osinbajo and APC’s national leader Bola Tinubu are top contenders for the APC tickets.
